yum yum YUM! since i modified this recipe i'm not going to rate it, but i'd give my variation a 3.5. i used legs and thighs instead of a whole chicken, and 2 lbs. rather than 3. i also added capers, and my olive oil was from a jar of sun- dried tomatoes. everything else, i used as directed. i ended up having to take the chicken out early (45 min.) since chicken parts cook more quickly. at that point the veggies were still stewlike, so i added in a can of cannellini beans, and since i couldn't resist, some white wine and chicken broth paste. i cooked it all together until the liquid mostly evaporated. and, well, oh my GOD! it is delicious! so good in fact that i'm making another batch of the veggies and beans tonight, to have more to eat with the chicken. yum.... the herbes de provence, esp. the lavender, gives it its distinctive flavor. i found it a bit strange at first, but it's lovely and unusual - along with the olives (i used kalamatas), it's a definite update on the standard onion/garlic/tomato- meat/starch one-pot- meal motif.

