Rating: 4
(Comments are for double the serving) This was a hit at dinner tonite! To make my Friday night dinner for 7pm for 8 people manageable, I chopped up all the veggies the night before, seasoned them & then put them in ziploc baggies. Per the reviews I added much more veggies (10 tomatoes,baby red potatoes, 3 large yellow onions, 2 1/4 olives & a handful of skinny, baby carrots) & was generous with the olive oil. The scent of the veggies by themselves as I was mixing them in the bowl was simply divine! I couldn't wait to cook it today. I also did the same thing with the chicken (seasoned & put in a bag with a half a lemon inside & fennel/anise stalk). Tonite all I had to do was open the bags & dump their contents in my roasting pan . By the way, I couldn't find a baking dish large enough for two 3.5 birds together in one dish that's why I used a roasting pan (it was the perfect reason for me to finally invest in an All Clad one!). Inspired by one of the reviews I brushed the tops of my chicken with maple syrup before putting in the oven. About a third of the way through I brushed their tops with olive oil. My guest raved when they walked in the door & everyone had seconds. I served this over Asian Jasmine rice. The chicken was falling off the bone. Highly recommend it! Next time will use capers & find fennel seeds.

