This meal is amazing! I cooked it for the first time for my husband, mother-in-law, sis-in-law & her children and they were just floored with this dish. First off, when I placed it on the table they started ooohing & aahing because the vegetables looked so beautiful & the chicken was perfect golden brown. I was kinda nervous coz I didn't know how it would taste. Then they started eating and they just couldn't get enough. After seeing their reaction, I ate starting with the onions. Wow, the onions were so sweet & tender! The chicken was really moist & tender too (coz of all the yummy juices). I started raving about the dish as if I wasn't the one who cooked it! I definitely recommend this meal. Delicious yet easy to cook. I added a lot more vegetables than was called for the recipe. Instead of 1 I put in 5 large yellow onions, 8 tomatoes instead of 4 and I added about 10 yukon gold potatoes which everybody just loved. It's a bit tight when you place everything on the baking dish but it certainly was more than enough for 4 adults & 2 children, even w/ just 1 whole chicken. I adjusted the rest of the recipe accordingly (except for the chicken) to accommodate the additional vegetables. Plus I added 15 minutes to the baking time to make the chicken skin a bit more crispier. Yum! Will be doing this meal A LOT!

