Rating: 4
This dish was absolutley delicious! I used chicken thighs and legs (Bell and Evans), seasoned them with the wet salt/herb rub under the skin and browned them in a cast iron pan. I started baking the veggies while the chicken was browning. I added about 1 cup of white wine to the veggies after they were cooking for a while. When the chicken was almost browned, I added more of the wet rub thinned out with the juice of 1/2 lemon over the chicken and let it cook for a few more minutes. I then added the chicken to the roasting veggies (on top) and they continued to bake and brown beautifully. I also added some of the pan drippings to the roasting chicken and veggies. I decided to braise some thinly sliced fennel until it was carmelized and tender. I mixed the fennel in with the roasted veggies just prior to plating - this was a delicious addition and would make this a permanent part of the recipe.

